Textbook 1.2.5 problem 8

Recreate the following visualization. What aesthetic should bill_depth_mm be mapped to? And should it be mapped at the global level or at the geom level?

#recreate visulalization
ggplot(penguins,aes(flipper_length_mm,body_mass_g)) +
  geom_point(aes(color=bill_depth_mm),size=2) +
  geom_smooth()
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula = 'y ~ x'

#bill_depth_mm 컬럼은 color로 aes에서 mapping 되었다
#bill_depth_mm 컬럼은 geom수준에서 매핑되어야합니다
#global에서 매핑될경우 geom_smooth에도 영향을 줍니다
#bill_depth_mm은 수치형 변수라서 geom_smooth에서 작동을 못합니다

Textbook 1.5.5 problem 6

Why does the following yield two separate legends? How would you fix it to combine the two legends?

ggplot(
  data = penguins,
  mapping = aes(
    x = bill_length_mm, y = bill_depth_mm, 
    color = species, shape = species
  )
) +
  geom_point() +
  labs(color = "Species")

주어진 코드에서 Species로 labs 이름을 지정하여서 species 컬럼과 분리되어서 범례가 보인다. 단순히 labs()를 없애거나 shape=“Species”를 추가하면 된다.

다음은 고친 코드와 결과이다

ggplot(
  data = penguins,
  mapping = aes(
    x = bill_length_mm, y = bill_depth_mm, 
    color = species, shape = species
  )
) +
  geom_point() +
  labs(color = "Species",shape="Species") #labs는 없어도 범례가 하나로 보인다

Textbook 9.4.1 problem 7

Recreate the following plot using facet_wrap() instead of facet_grid(). How do the positions of the facet labels change?

ggplot(mpg) + 
  geom_point(aes(x = displ, y = hwy)) +
  facet_grid(drv ~ .)

다음은 고친 코드이다

ggplot(mpg) + 
  geom_point(aes(x = displ, y = hwy)) +
  facet_wrap(~drv)

#facet label이 우측에서 위로 간것을 볼 수 있다

Textbook 12.5.4 problem 3

se if_else() to compute the absolute value of a numeric vector called x.

ab <- function(x) {
  return(if_else(x>=0,x,-x))
}
x <- c(15, -30, 0, -20)
ab(x)
## [1] 15 30  0 20

flights %>% 
  group_by(dest) %>% 
  mutate(total_delay=sum(arr_delay,na.rm=TRUE)) %>% 
  mutate(prop_delay=arr_delay/total_delay) %>% 
  select(prop_delay, total_delay, colnames(flights))

flights %>% 
  filter(arr_delay>=0) %>% 
  group_by(dest) %>% 
  mutate(total_delay=sum(arr_delay,na.rm=TRUE)) %>% 
  mutate(prop_delay=arr_delay/total_delay) %>%
